Effective Date: [20/11/24]

Aida ("we," "our," "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you interact with Aida Virtual Assistant, a chatbot integrated into Discord, available through GitHub.

By using Aida Virtual Assistant, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.
1. Information We Collect

When you use Aida Virtual Assistant, we may collect the following types of information:

    Discord User Information: We may collect basic Discord account information, such as your username and user ID, in order to interact with you and provide personalized responses.
    Messages and Conversations: The content of your conversations with Aida Virtual Assistant may be stored for the purpose of improving the chatbot’s functionality and enhancing user experience. We do not store personal messages or data without your knowledge.
    Technical Data: We may automatically collect certain technical information such as your device type, browser version, and operating system for debugging and improving the application.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

    Provide Services: To respond to your queries and provide relevant information as requested by the user through the chatbot.
    Improve Functionality: To improve and optimize Aida Virtual Assistant’s performance, ensuring it meets the needs and expectations of users.
    Enhance User Experience: To provide personalized assistance based on user interactions.

3. Data Retention

We retain conversation data and other technical information to improve the functionality and quality of Aida Virtual Assistant. Conversations and data may be stored temporarily for analysis and improvements. However, we do not retain personal data indefinitely.
4. How We Protect Your Information

We take the security of your information seriously. All communication with Aida Virtual Assistant is encrypted, and we implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
5. Sharing Your Information

We do not share, sell, or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share data with third-party service providers that help us operate and maintain Aida Virtual Assistant, as necessary. These third parties are required to keep your information confidential and use it only for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy.
6. Your Rights

You have the right to:

    Request Access: You may request to view the information we have collected about you.
    Request Deletion: You may request the deletion of your personal data from our records.
    Opt-Out: If you no longer wish to interact with Aida Virtual Assistant, you may opt-out at any time by disabling or leaving the Discord server.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. When updates occur, the date at the top of the Privacy Policy will be updated. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
8. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at:

    GitHub Repository: [https://github.com/SlickAsAlways/Aida-Discord-Bot]
    Email: [brandondevonport123@gmail.com]
